description:
TimeSyncIO: Table recording time synchronization I/O parameters for Ericsson radio equipment.

dateTime: Timestamp of the time synchronization I/O record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
Id3:  Generic identifier (value is '1' in sample data).
Id4: Generic identifier (value is '1' in sample data).
vsDataType: Type of data, indicating time synchronization I/O data.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format (EricssonSpecificAttributes).
TimeSyncIO.encapsulation: Encapsulation information specifying the network hierarchy and equipment involved.
TimeSyncIO.timeSyncIOId: ID for the time synchronization I/O.
TimeSyncIO.compensationDelay: Compensation delay value.
TimeSyncIO.reservedBy: Information on the equipment reserving the time synchronization I/O resource.
TimeSyncIO.filterTime: Filter time value (likely in some unit of time).
queries: Show me all TimeSyncIO records from NR_Balikpapan with compensationDelay > 10ms.
What is the average compensationDelay for CellId 12345 in the last 24 hours?
Retrieve all TimeSyncIO entries where vsDataFormatVersion is not '1.0'.
Find the distinct Area_Name values associated with TimeSyncIO.timeSyncIOId = 'XYZ123'.
How many TimeSyncIO records have a filterTime less than 1 second for CellId starting with '678'?
